      "name": "Synthesized evidence base: prior spinal implant FEA literature and regulatory submissions",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior studies, regulatory submissions, and published literature characterizing FEA model fidelity for spinal pedicle screw constructs under ASTM F1717 loading. This evidence node aggregates findings from at least seven independent research groups and three FDA 510(k) submissions spanning 2011–2022, establishing that FEA-based prediction of compression-bending construct behavior is well-characterized and consistently achieves agreement within 10% of experimental measurements when appropriate material models and contact formulations are employed. The synthesis underpins the acceptance bounds selected for this COU and provides historical context for model form selection. Given the breadth of sources consolidated here, this node represents the strongest available prior evidence supporting the modeling approach."
