  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou1-noncannulated-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-cdrh-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) reflects the limitation of a single quasi-static loading rate, which is accepted given that ASTM F1717 specifies quasi-static conditions as the normative test protocol and the COU decision consequence is medium. All three primary QoIs satisfy the pre-established acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96 and mean difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is assessed as sufficiently credible to support the intended regulatory decision for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
